\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\cf1\kerning0\b0\f1\fs28 EXTREMELY IMPORTANT:\cf0\par
\fs18 In order to use DAD you must install several pieces of software that we cannot redistribute legally.  We have included links here that you can use to go directly to the download page for a known DAD compatible version of these tools.\par
\par
\pard\b\fs20 http://downloads.activestate.com/ActivePerl/Windows/5.8/ActivePerl-5.8.8.817-MSWin32-x86-257965.msi\par
http://dev.mysql.com/get/Downloads/MySQL-5.0/mysql-5.0.37-win32.zip/from/pick\par
http://www.php.net/get/php-5.2.1-win32-installer.msi/from/a/mirror\par
\par
Before proceeding you should download these packages.  You should install Perl and MySQL.  Do NOT install PHP until AFTER the Apache installation has completed during the installation script.\par
\pard\keepn\s2\sb240\sa60\sl276\slmult1\i\f0\fs28 MySQL\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\b0\i0\f1\fs20 Using the MySQL installer that you have downloaded, perform a typical install by accepting all of the defaults.  If you wish to perform a more detailed installation and configuration, you can choose to exclude the InnoDB database engine since we use the MySQL engine exclusively.  It is not necessary to perform a MySQL.com Sign-Up during the installation though you are welcome to do so.  When asked about configuration options, please be sure to configure MySQL to start as a service.  It is also recommended that you configure the installer to put MySQL in your path.\par
\par
If after 'executing' the installation, it may prompt saying that the service is not enable or there is a firewall turned on. Ensure that the firewall is off of that the port is allowed to communicate. Also, the service simply maybe slow to start, so you should 'retry' on the 'error' window.\par
\b\par
\pard\keepn\s2\sb240\sa60\sl276\slmult1\i\f0\fs28 Perl\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\b0\i0\f1\fs20 Using the installer that you have downloaded, please complete a default installation of Perl.  You can accept all of the defaults to complete the installation most easily.\par
\pard\keepn\s2\sb240\sa60\sl276\slmult1\b\i\f0\fs28 PHP\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\i0\f1\fs20 AFTER Apache has been installed and when the installation script prompts you to, you should install the PHP package that you downloaded.  \b0 Using the PHP 5 installer that you downloaded, please perform a standard installation of PHP.  During the installation process you should select support for a \b "Apache 2.0.x"\b0  server.  You \b must\b0  also configure PHP to install the GD2, MySQL and MySQLi modules.\par
\par
